NAME - program.c

USAGE - 
$ make
$ make run

DESCRIPTION - 
Counts the number of capital letters in hello.txt and demo.txt and writes the count in count.txt.

Example -
$ make
gcc -c program.c
gcc -o fileWrite program.o

$ make run
./fileWrite

$ cat count.txt 
Capital letters in hello.txt are 2.
Capital letters in demo.txt are 3.
